<br>
You can bind wounds to about 60% if you have the patience for it, by removing any HP gear you may have.<br>
<br>
Here's how it works, mathmatically.<br>
<br>
If you have 1000 HP total, normally you could bind wounds to about 490 or so (at 495 or so, you'll get a message saying you can't bind over 50%). If you take off any gear that gives you HP (NOT Stamina gear) you might drop your HP down to say 850. BUT the HP Gear takes off full HP.<br>
<br>
In this case, you were at 490/1000. You go to 340/850. You can fit in a few more bind wounds, and get to about 415 or so. Put your gear back on, and Poof. You end up at about 565/1000. Mend, and you should be in pretty good shape.<br>
<br>
I don't believe this to be an exploit. The numbers here are a concept proof, not an actual guide, but I usually end up well above 50%. <br>
<br>
The reason this doesn't work as well (or much at all) with Sta gear is because gear that gives you stamina takes an appropriate % of full HP/potential HP.<br>
<br>
Thanks! I hope this helps!<br>
<br>
Xenom L45 Monk of Dhoom.<br>
