<br>
Idea: you finish a fight and go to bandage. You replace an orc fang earring with a 5 stamina earring, your 6/65 rings with 7 stamina rings. Now, your current hp has dropped by 145hp, but your total HP has only dropped by a little. So you can bind back up to 50% of your normal hit points instead of your naked HP, then swap back in your HP gear to get those HP on top of it.<br>
<br>
Putting on/taking off stamina gear only changes your maximum HP. Putting on/taking off HP gear changes both your max HP and current HP. You can actually use this to your advantage if you need a couple hundred extra HP for a fight too. Wear your stamina gear, heal up to full, start fighting, when you go down a little bit, start replacing stamina gear with HP gear.<br>
<br>
Way too much trouble for me to bother with, but possible nonetheless.<br>
<br>
Also good for twinks, who tend to have insane amounts of +HP gear. My level 16 shadowknight can bind wound to something like 80%. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uchokal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chokal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/6/02 10:52:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1066.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &lt;L50 bind wounds assistance:</span><hr size=1> I do this as well, one thing I have found out though is don't remove all of your hp adding gear until you are about to hit 50% or what ever your max bind is.  I took, or well tried, to take mine all off before I started binding and well after "Loading, Please wait...." I didn't have to worry about binding LOL. <p><center><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=62214">Montor Lyzzard - Noble of the Avengers Federation</a><br>
